<rt.Mana>Tanks</> are primarily responsible for managing the following mechanics:

  •   <rt.Mana>Threat</>
      •   Heroes generate <rt.Bold>Threat</> on enemies by doing damage to them or healing allies.
      •   The first hero seen by an enemy generates an <rt.Bold>initial burst</> of Threat.
      •   Tanks generate 350% more threat compared to Damage Dealers and Healers.

  •   <rt.Mana>Aggro</>
      •   Whoever has the highest Threat has an enemies’ <rt.Bold>Aggro</>.
      •   When a hero has an enemies’ Aggro, the enemy will generally attempt to prioritize attacking this target.

<rt.Mana>Tank Tips:</>
  •   Due to the initial increased threat, tanks should be the <rt.Bold>first</> to initiate fights.
  •   Every tank has a <rt.Bold>’Taunt’</> ability. 
           •   This ability will immediately set the tank to the highest threat for an enemy.
  •   When allies have Aggro on enemies, the best way to help the tank get them off is to <rt.Bold>stay close</> to the tank.
  •   Tanks have great <rt.Bold>Crowd Control</>, they often have abilities to <rt.Bold>Interrupt, Slow, Stun, and Reposition</> enemies.
  •   When fighting dangerous enemies with frontal attacks and cleaves, try to face them <rt.Bold>away</> from your allies.

<rt.bold>Helena</> is a Melee <rt.Mana>Tank</> that uses <rt.bold>Builder/Spender Mechanics</>.
She excels in the front lines taking hits instead of her allies.
Helena uses Combo Points to perform powerful attacks and generate Toughness.
Toughness is her main resource for mitigating incoming damage and surviving dangerous attacks.

Helena's primary power stat is <rt.Bold>Strength</>. All damage she deals is affected by this stat.
534EB35B488E6425673C1CB0D725CA1E:
<rt.bold>Meiko</> is a Melee <rt.Mana>Tank</> that uses <rt.bold>Ability Combo Mechanics</>.
She excels in the front lines taking hits instead of her allies.
She uses Ability Combos to perform powerful Finishing Moves.
Big cooldowns and self buffs give her survivability and self-healing.

Meiko's primary power stat is <rt.Bold>Agility</>. All damage she deals is affected by this stat.
8DE2DB6149F944D868F391A39D497A48:
<rt.bold>RIGHT CLICK</> on an enemy to enter a <rt.italic>combat stance</>.

<rt.primarystat>Melee</> heroes will <rt.meikoability3>auto attack</> the targeted enemy if they are in front of them, in-range while in <rt.italic>combat stance</>.

<rt.bold>Rime</> is a <rt.meikoability1>Damage Dealer</>.

<rt.bold>Rime</> is a Spellcasting <rt.debuff>Damage Dealer</> that uses <rt.bold>Builder/Spender Mechanics</>.
She excels at focusing down the biggest threat from a distance.
Many of Rime’s abilities fill an Anima Bar to deal spikes of damage and generate Winter Orbs.
She uses Winter Orbs to cast dangerous spells.

Rime's primary power stat is Intellect. All damage she deals is affected by this stat.
5EB328934343734410787BB0E36881CF:
<rt.bold>Sylvie</> is a <rt.heal>Healer</> that uses <rt.bold>Pet Management Mechanics</>.

She excels at sending her pets to heal her allies over time and attack her enemies.
She commands her Flutterflies and Plants to heal, and her Boomshrooms to attack enemies.
Her Heal over Time spells force her to plan ahead in battle.

Sylvie's primary power stat is Intellect. All damage and healing she deals is affected by this stat.
2907B13F40E2330CAC2EAB886A5CB13F: <rt.bold>Sylvie</>, a <rt.meikoability2>Healer</>, has emerged from hiding to join your party!
217E9FEC465A8CC38278559DB90C4B08:
<rt.bold>Tariq</> is a Melee <rt.debuff>Damage Dealer</> that uses <rt.bold>Builder/Spender</> and <rt.bold>Timing Mechanics</>.
He excels in the front lines flanking his enemies.
Timing his abilities around his Swing Timer will maximize his damage and Fury generation.
He uses Fury to perform powerful attacks.

Tariq's primary power stat is Strength. All damage he deals is affected by this stat.
BD69B42C477CE40BAFF2EEB88DF2A981:
<rt.bold>Vigour</> is a <rt.heal>Healer</> that uses <rt.bold>Builder/Spender Mechanics</>.

He excels in the middle of his allies where he can sustain them with powerful AoE heals.
As a wielder of Radiant Runes, he must choose how and when to cast his most powerful spells.
His Direct Healing allows him to react quickly to an ever-changing battlefield.

Vigour's primary power stat is Intellect. All damage and healing he deals is affected by this stat.
05F0994D4BDC180F45E0D4AEE41D13D0:
<rt.debuff>Damage Dealers (DPS)</> are primarily responsible for the following mechanics:
  •   <rt.debuff>Crowd Control (CC)</>
      •   Every Damage Dealer Hero has abilities than can <rt.Bold>Interrupt, Slow, Stun, and/or Reposition</> enemies.
           •    These should be used frequently to increase your party’s chances of survival.
           •    More of these abilities unlock upon completing higher mission difficulties.
      •   Enemy abilities that are interruptible are indicated by <rt.Bold>Yellow Cast Bars</> underneath enemy Health Bars.

  •   <rt.debuff>Dealing Damage</>
      •   Every hero has a <rt.Bold>Core Rotation</>, which is usually the optimal use of several abilities for best effect.
           •    For Damage Dealers especially, learning their Core Rotation, and when to deviate is the key to mastery!
      •   Damage Dealer Heroes define the duration of combat as they generally deal the majority of the damage.
      •   Keeping an eye on the <rt.Bold>Damage Meter</> helps to compare the damage across the group.
           •   The Damage Meter is also a good indicator to understand how well you are playing.
      •   Many damaging abilities excel at either <rt.Bold>single-target damage</>, or dealing damage to <rt.Bold>groups of enemies</>.

  •  <rt.debuff>Surviving</>
      •   Keep an eye on the battlefield to avoid dangerous enemy attacks! 
           •    A dead Damage Dealer kills nothing.
      •   Damage Dealers have at least one ability to help them with <rt.Bold>mobility</> and to <rt.Bold>reduce incoming damage</>.

<rt.debuff>Damage Dealer Tips:</>
  •   Don't stand in <rt.Bold>Area of Effect spells</> on the ground. Use mobility and damage mitigation abilities to survive!
  •   Use <rt.Bold>[Tab]</> to quickly cycle through enemies that are in front of you.
  •   Pick your targets wisely!
      •   Focusing on the most dangerous enemy with the other Damage Dealer can protect your party.
      •   Attacking the target of the tank can help you avoid getting <rt.Bold>Aggro</>.
      •   Finishing off enemies with low health will support your Tank and Healer.

<rt.gold>Asha’s Dilemma</> adds a potential ‘Fail’ state to missions.

Failing to kill all Bosses and complete the Kill Score within the allotted time will be considered a ‘Fail’.

The only negative impact this has for you is that it will lower the High Score for the mission on the <rt.gold>Leaderboard</> dramatically, and prevent you unlocking progression and higher difficulties for that run. 

Regroup and try again!
36C9274049F9D95FE6349FA64F12D2A5:
<rt.gold>Asha’s Dilemma</> is an Ascension that is active on all Dungeons and Adventures with a +4 Difficulty and higher. 

Failing to time a Dungeon lowers the Dungeon Rating for the attempt.

<rt.Bold>Adventures</> have a 8-16 minute timer.
<rt.Bold>Dungeons</> have a 28-36 minute timer.
90A8A9D3473301CC9AA410958888169A:
<rt.gold>Campsites</> act as checkpoints for your progress. If you die in battle, you will always respawn at the last campsite your party has activated.

The path ahead looks pretty manageable, but better safe than sorry!
4F03F0B74F606BD5702089B45CC8DD25:
<rt.gold>Equipment</> can be Reforged using <rt.bold>Mithril</>.

Reforging an item <rt.italic>resets its Item Level to what it was obtained at</> but, depending on what type of <rt.bold>Mithril</> ingot you use, you can change or maintain its slot type.

Reforging is a way of 'rerolling' high value equipment that are not exactly what you are looking for, but are too valuable to scrap into their material components.
EACD379041911F1233760DAD9BCDFC6D:
<rt.gold>Find Game</> is for players who want to play specific dungeons and difficulties, but don't want the responsibility of hosting a group!

Click the <rt.bold>’Find Game’</> button to be matched with a player from the <rt.gold>Host Game</> queue who is looking to run one of your desired dungeons and align with your filters.

You can select multiple <rt.bold>Adventures</> and <rt.bold>Dungeons</> to expand your search options.
With multiple selected, use the arrows at the top of the screen to preview missions and see their specific loot and modifiers.
224E5A654A682DFB211770847CA5372E:
<rt.gold>Gems</> can be <rt.gold>Fused</> and <rt.gold>Transmuted</> by spending <rt.gold>Aether</>.

<rt.gold>Fusing</> Gems requires three of the same size and color be converted into one gem of the next highest level. There is <rt.italic>no cost</> to split a Gem into three of the next lowest level, however.

<rt.gold>Transmuting</> Gems will use <rt.gold>Aether</> to turn the gem into one of a different color, so you don't have gems that are not being used in your loadout.

<rt.italic>It is not possible to destroy or lose gems</>, only to Fuse, Split, or Transmute them.
9BC2AE67421BD4A6D3A2B69CD0641F82:
<rt.gold>Host Game</> is for players who want to play specific dungeons and difficulties.

Click the <rt.bold>’Find Players’</> button to be matched with players from the <rt.gold>Find Game</> queue who are looking to run similar content and align with your filters.
BEBFABCE4D9F19322BB4F1BFFF792A68:
<rt.gold>Quickplay</> is the fastest way to get into a mission and perfect for anyone new to the game!

Click 'Play' to be matched with up to three other players and thrown into a short single-boss <rt.bold>Dungeon</>. 

The difficulty will be automatically set to the experience and competence of the party. 

<rt.bold>Dungeons</> take about 10-15 minutes to complete.

<rt.gold>Quickplay</> will outfit your hero with basic equipment and quickly assemble a party to send you into a <rt.bold>Dungeon</>.
E36EB4C1419569784C8BA596E51CBF0A:
<rt.gold>Scrap</> your unwanted Equipment at the <rt.gold>Artificer</> for extra resources!

Gold and Materia will drop in higher quantities as mission difficulty increases.

Both are used for <rt.Bold>Upgrades</>, but are also useful for <rt.Bold>Reforging</> and <rt.Bold>Transmutation</> as you reach higher difficulties.

9076C74640EB8C3C7ABF9981E0ED84FE:
<rt.heal>Healers</> are primarily responsible for the following mechanics:
  •   <rt.heal>Healing & Damage Mitigation</>
      •   Healers are defined by their capacity to <rt.Bold>heal, absorb, or mitigate damage</> with powerful spells.
      •   Keeping a Tank alive indirectly keeps your Damage Dealers alive as well.

  •   <rt.heal>Dispelling Debuffs</>
      •   Enemies will often cast <rt.Bold>dangerous curses or debuffs</> on the party.
      •   Healers can remove these, <rt.Bold>defined by icons outlined in blue</>, with their <rt.Bold>Dispel</>.

  •  <rt.heal>Mana Management</>
      •   All Healers use Mana as a resource when they <rt.Bold>cast healing spells</>.
      •   Mana regenerates <rt.Bold>very slowly in combat</> and <rt.Bold>more quickly when out of combat</>.
      •   Healers need to be <rt.Bold>efficient with the ability choices</> to preserve their Mana during long encounters.
      •   <rt.Bold>Overhealing</> an ally will <rt.Bold>waste Mana</>, so use damage mitigating abilities or offensive spells when allies are full health.

<rt.heal>Healer Tips:</>
  •   Use offensive abilities when the party does not need healing. <rt.Bold>Every bit of damage counts!</>
  •   Use Party Frames above the Ability Bar (by default) to quickly assess and select party members to heal.
  •   By default, all healers default to casting heals on mouse-over target allies.
  •   Healers shouldn’t forget to heal themself. <rt.Bold>A dead healer typically leads to a dead party!</>

Despite being weighed down by full plate armor, Helena is always ready to charge into the fray to protect her companions.

Helena is a Melee Tank and excels in the front lines taking hits instead of her allies.

Her Veteran of War mechanic allows Helena to reduce the cooldowns of her ability to allow for more frequent use of her powerful attacks and Toughness generators.

Toughness is Helena's main resource for mitigating incoming damage and surviving dangerous encounters. Her Toughness is shown as a blue bar to the right of the character.

Disillusioned after the Twelve Year War, Helena wandered the world fighting back evil where noble apathy or cruelty allowed it to fester.

Helena is a close-combat hero, and fights mainly in melee range.
Enemies need to be selected, close, and in front of her.

Helena’s unique Hero Mechanics:
  •   <rt.Mana>Combo Points</> are your Builder/Spender resource
      •   Max 5 Combo Points can be held at a time.
      •   These are built by using certain abilities, such as <rt.Bold>Measured Strike</> or <rt.Bold>Powerful Strike</>.
      •   These are spent by using other abilities, such as <rt.Bold>Shield Bash</>.

  •   <rt.Mana>Toughness</> is a passive Damage Mitigation resource.
      •   This is gained by using certain abilities, such as <rt.Bold>Shields Up</>, and by blocking. 
      •   Toughness will automatically reduce incoming damage by a percentage depending on your current Toughness.
      •   Every time Toughness reduces damage taken it will deplete proportionally to the amount of damage mitigated.

  •   <rt.Mana>Spirit Ability - Leader’s Conviction</>
      •   Helena gains 100% Toughness for 12 sec. Toughness does not deplete for the duration of this effect.
      •   Helena also gains 30% haste for 20 seconds.

<rt.Mana>Helena Tips:</>
  •   Use Combo Point Spenders before you generate more than you can use.
  •   <rt.Bold>Charge</> and can help Helena quickly catch distant enemies.
  •   <rt.Bold>Chain Pull</> is best used to reposition ranged enemies and casters.
  •   When an enemy ability cannot be interrupted or sidestepped, use <rt.Bold>Shields Up</> to survive.
  •   <rt.Bold>Shockwave</> is best used generating threat and to slow enemies so Helena can safely reposition or move out of danger.

D7E8AEE0439C124663D4A1BDE97C43BF:
Meiko is a close-combat hero, and fights mainly in melee range.
Enemies need to be selected, close, and in front of her.

Meiko’s unique Hero Mechanics:
  •   <rt.Mana>Ability Combos</> require <rt.bold>Combo Builders</> to use powerful <rt.bold>Finishing Moves</>
      •   <rt.meikoability1>Spirit Palm</>, <rt.meikoability2>Wind Kick</>, and <rt.meikoability3>Earth Fist</> are Combo Builders
      •   Combining two Combo Builders will grant Meiko access to a <rt.Bold>Finishing Move</>.
           •   Read the Finishing Move tooltip on your ability bar for a full list of abilities and descriptions.
      •   <rt.meikoability1>Palm Technique</> Finishing Moves grant <rt.Bold>offensive and defensive buffs</>.
      •   <rt.meikoability2>Kick Technique</> Finishing Moves empower and deal <rt.Bold>multi-target attacks</>.
      •   <rt.meikoability3>Fist Technique</> Finishing Moves empower and deal <rt.Bold>single target attacks</>.

  •   <rt.Mana>Survival Abilities</> 
      •   Meiko must rely on <rt.Bold>self-buffs and big cooldown abilities</> to survive.
      •   <rt.Bold>Stone Shield</> is Meiko’s main source of <rt.Bold>Armor</> and damage mitigation.
      •   <rt.Bold>Serenity</> slowly charges up from Auto Attacking that Meiko can use to heal herself.
      •   <rt.Bold>Twin Souls: Bulwark</> turns all enemy Aggro towards a stone duplicate of yourself.
           •    Use this when you are about to be overwhelmed to buy yourself time to recover.

  •  <rt.Mana>Spirit Ability - Twin Souls: Army of One</>
      •   Meiko embodies the <rt.Bold>Sibling of Earth</>, taking 40% reduced damage for a short duration.
      •   <rt.Bold>Siblings of Wind</> will teleport and attack nearby enemies.
      •   Meiko also gains 30% haste for 20 seconds.

<rt.Mana>Meiko Tips:</>

E2B87E784A96FF522DF704BAA0ED530B:
Rime is a ranged hero, and can cast spells from a distance. 
Enemies need to be selected, within range, and in front of her.

Rime’s unique Hero Mechanics:
  •   <rt.debuff>Anima</> fills up your <rt.Bold>Anima Bar</>.
      •   Anima is generated when you use certain abilities, such as <rt.Bold>Frost Bolt</> or <rt.Bold>Freezing Torrent</>.
      •   When the Anima Bar becomes full, Rime gains a <rt.Bold>Winter Orb</> and summons <rt.Bold>Anima Spikes</> to strike her target.
      •   After the Winter Orb and Anima Spikes have been summoned, the Anima Bar resets back to 0.

  •   <rt.debuff>Winter Orbs</> are your Builder/Spender resource
      •   Max 5 Winter Orbs can be held at a time.
      •   These are built by filling the Anima Bar or using certain abilities, such as Cold Snap.
      •   Winter Orbs are spent to cast powerful damaging abilities, such as <rt.Bold>Glacial Blast</> or <rt.Bold>Ice Comet</>.

  •   <rt.debuff>Spirit Ability - Wrath of Winter</>
      •   Rime passively shoots Anima Spikes at enemies, and generates a Winter Orb every 2 seconds for 20 seconds.
      •   All damage dealt is increased by 15% for the duration of this effect.
      •   Rime also gains 30% haste for 20 seconds.

<rt.debuff>Rime Tips:</>
  •   Use Winter Orb Spenders before you generate more than you can use.
  •   Change what abilities you spend Winter Orbs on based on the encounter: Single Target or Multi Target.
  •   Use <rt.Bold>Ice Dash, Frost Ward, and Winter’s Blessing</> to survive dangerous enemy abilities!

Sylvie is a healer who uses her innate connection to nature and its many friends to heal her allies and harm her foes.

Sylvie is a Healer that uses Pet Management Mechanics. She excels at sending her pets to heal her allies over time and attack her enemies.

She commands her Flutterflies and Plants to heal allies and attack enemies.

Her powerful Heal over Time spells allow her to prepare for battle and endure long and sustained fights.
1E1092ED45161B43EC68689364122170:
Sylvie is a ranged hero, and fights mainly from a distance. Most of her abilities are instant cast.
Enemies need to be selected, within range, in front of her for offensive abilities.
Allies generally only need to be within range and be targeted for healing abilities.

Sylvie’s unique Hero Mechanics:
  •   <rt.heal>Pet Management</> is critical with four different pets types:
      •   <rt.meikoability1>Pink Flutterflies</> are the foundation of Sylvie’s healing.
           •    Sylvie has 4 of these.
           •    Syvlie can assign these to stay with and heal allies with her ability; <rt.Bold>Fluttercall: Heal</>.
           •    Only <rt.Bold>one</> Pink Flutterfly can be assigned to an ally at a time.
           •    <rt.Bold>Fluttercall: Restore Life</> will send two Pink Flutterflies to an ally. 
                 •    Afterwards the two Pink Flutterflies will return to Sylvie as unassigned.
           •    Pink Flutterflies are unassigned by default, but will remain assigned to an ally until called away.
                 •    Assigning a Pink Flutterfly ability will prioritize taking from unassigned Pink Flutterflies.
                 •    If no Pink Flutterflies are unassigned, then it will take from allies with the <rt.Bold>highest health</>.

      •   <rt.mana>Blue Flutterfly</> helps Sylvie alternate between healing a single ally, or several.
           •    Sylvie has one of these.
           •    The Blue Flutterfly is assigned to Sylvie by default.
           •    <rt.Bold>Fluttercall: Protect</> will assign the Blue Flutterfly to a single ally.
                 •    This will <rt.Bold>increase the amount of healing</> the ally receives from Pink Flutterflies.
           •    <rt.Bold>Fluttercall: Embrace</> will assign the Blue Flutterfly back to Sylvie.
                 •    Assigning the Blue Flutterfly to Sylvie increases the healing of <rt.Bold>all Pink Flutterflies</>.
                 •    The mana cost of all of Sylvie’s spells is <rt.Bold>reduced</>.

      •   <rt.meikoability2>Plants</> deal damage to Sylvie’s enemies and can heal allies.
           •    Sylvie can summon <rt.Bold>Prickly Vines, Life Petals, and Heart Blooms</>.
                 •    <rt.Bold>Prickly Vines</> will attack whichever enemy Sylvie is targeting when summoned.
                       •    These attack the enemy Sylvie is currently targeting when summoned.
                       •    If their target dies, they will attack the enemy closest to them in combat.
                       •    Sylvie’s ability <rt.Bold>Rootsap Revival</> will cause all Prickly Vines to heal a target ally.
                 •    <rt.Bold>Life Petals</> will heal the ally with the lowest health.
                 •    <rt.Bold>Heart Blooms</> heals all allies based on the amount of all the current Pink Flutterfly healing.
      •   <rt.warning>Boomshrooms</> spawn when summoned plants expire.
           •    Boomshrooms take a <rt.Bold>short period of time</> to mature after spawning.
           •    <rt.Bold>Shroomsplosion</> will send all <rt.Bold>mature</> Boomshrooms to explode on Sylvie's target.
           •    Each Plant spawns a <rt.Bold>different amount</> of Boomshrooms when they expire.
                 •    Prickly Vines spawn <rt.Bold>one</> Boomshroom when they expire.
                 •    Life Petals spawn <rt.Bold>two</> Boomshrooms when they expire.
                 •    Heart Blooms spawn <rt.Bold>three</> Boomshrooms when they expire.
           •    Boomshrooms will <rt.Bold>eventually expire</> if they are not used by Shroomsplosion

  •   <rt.heal>Healing Over Time</> is integral to Sylvie’s playstyle
      •   Sylvie does not have any direct healing, and must rely on preparing her pets to <rt.Bold>heal allies over time</>.
      •   The <rt.Bold>main source of Sylvie’s healing</> comes from Pink Flutterflies and Plants.

  •   <rt.heal>Spirit Ability - Fluttercall: Jubilee</>
      •   Sylvie assigns <rt.Bold>Dream Flutterflies</> to all allies, which compiles the total health of the entire party and redestributes it evenly every 3 seconds.
      •   Sylvie also gains 30% haste for 20 seconds.

<rt.heal>Sylvie Tips:</>
  •   Always keep<rt.Bold>Pink Flutterflies</> assigned to allies. They are not useful when they are unassigned.
  •   Reassign Pink Flutterflies to allies after using <rt.Bold>Fluttercall: Restore Life</>.
  •   <rt.Bold>Pink Flutterflies</> will remain assigned to an ally until they are called away or the ally dies.
  •   When Sylvie dies, <rt.Bold>all Flutterflies return to her</>. Pink Flutterflies reset to their unassigned state.
  •   Assign the <rt.Bold>Blue Flutterfly</> to the Tank when other players are not taking damage.
  •   <rt.Bold>Hidden Trail</> reduces the amount of threat Sylvie generates from her healing for a short period.

Tariq channels storm and fury to deal immense damage to his enemies.

Tariq is a Melee Damage Dealer that uses Builder/Spender and Timing Mechanics. He excels in the front lines to flank his enemies while they face the Tank.

Timing his abilities around his Swing Timer will maximize his damage and Fury generation.

Fury is required for Tariq to perform powerful attacks.
E786A6FE435A0A95AFB7E89B6A1734A8:
Tariq is a close-combat hero, and fights mainly in melee range with instant cast abilities.
Enemies need to be selected, within range, and in front of him.

Tariq’s unique Hero Mechanics:
  •   <rt.debuff>Swing Timer</> displays the timing on Tariq’s auto-attacks.
      •   If a <rt.Bold>Heavy Strike</> is readied when the Swing Timer triggers an auto-attack it will deal immense damage.
           •    All of Tariq’s other abilities will <rt.Bold>cancel</> Heavy Strike.
           •    Heavy strike should be the <rt.Bold>last ability</> used before the Swing Timer triggers an auto-attack.
           •    Heavy Strike must be cast before the timer passes the <rt.Bold>‘Red’ portion</> of the Swing Timer.
           •    This ability is <rt.Bold>not affected by Global Cooldowns</> (The minimum time between using abilities)
      •   Some abilities do not disrupt the Swing Timer, such as <rt.Bold>Wild Swing</> and <rt.Bold>Face Breaker</>.
      •   Some abilities interrupt and reset the Swing Timer, such as <rt.Bold>Skull Crusher</> and <rt.Bold>Hammer Storm</>.

  •   <rt.debuff>Fury</> is your Builder/Spender resource
      •   Max 100 Fury can be held at a time.
      •   This is built by dealing damage with some abilities, such as <rt.Bold>Heavy Strike</> and <rt.Bold>Wild Swing</>.
      •   Some abilities build a set amount of Fury, such as <rt.Bold>Leap Smash</> and <rt.Bold>Thunder Call</>.
      •   Fury is spent on powerful abilities like <rt.Bold>Skull Crusher</> and <rt.Bold>Hammer Storm</>.

  •   <rt.debuff>Thunder Call</> is an ability that empowers some of your other abilities for a short time.
      •   Heavy Strike deals more damage to your target, and also deals damage to <rt.Bold>enemies around your target</>.
      •   Fury Spenders, such as <rt.Bold>Skull Crusher</> and <rt.Bold>Hammer Storm</>, deal much higher damage.
      •   <rt.Bold>Chain Lightning</> can only be cast while Tariq is empowered by <rt.Bold>Thunder Call</>.

  •   <rt.debuff>Spirit Ability - Raging Tempest</>
      •   Tariq gains an <rt.Bold>enhanced form</> of Thundercall for a short duration.
      •   He also gains <rt.Bold>Raging Currents</> which strikes nearby enemies with lightning.
           •    In addition to dealing damage, each lightning strike also grants a bonus to Tariq’s <rt.Bold>Critical Hit chance</>.
      •   Tariq also gains 30% haste for 20 seconds.

<rt.debuff>Tariq:</>
  •   Squeeze in as many <rt.Bold>Wild Swings</> and <rt.Bold>Face Breakers</> into the Swing Timer before using <rt.Bold>Heavy Strike</>.
  •   <rt.Bold>Heavy Strike</> isn’t affected by Global Cooldowns, so you can use it instantly after another ability.
  •   <rt.Bold>Face Breaker</> deals damage but can only be used when you <rt.Bold>Miss</> your target.
      •   Try to use this ability quickly so the next miss can make it available again.
  •   <rt.Bold>Leap Smash</> can be used to deal damage, but it can also be used to avoid dangerous situations.
  •   <rt.Bold>Unbreakable Will</> can allow Tariq to <rt.Bold>Tank temporarily</>, by giving him a <rt.Bold>Taunt</> and mitigating damage.
      •   Use this ability defensively to survive, or to save an ally in danger.
      •   Taunting can cause the <rt.Bold>Tank to panic</> when they lose Aggro. Choose your targets wisely!
  •   <rt.Bold>Thunder Call</> should be used when facing groups of enemies or spending Fury.
  •   <rt.Bold>Intimidate</> will cause nearby enemies to flee in terror, but they will not run far.
  •   <rt.Bold>Culling Strike</> can deal immense damage to enemies with <rt.Bold>less than 30% health</>.

3A01C15B471FEF428770B6AABE8291EE: To the frozen south, high atop the Ael'deth Mountain, lies the hidden prison of Al’zerac, an ancient frost wyrm. For centuries, the Eldrin have guarded the vault, but time wears down both vigilance and faith. Cithrel now walks the outer wards, her power cracking ancient seals that once bound the Great Wyrm. Vigour is a ranged hero, and fights mainly from a distance. He casts most of his abilities.
Enemies need to be selected, within range, in front of him for offensive abilities.
Allies generally only need to be within range and be targeted for healing abilities.

Vigour’s unique Hero Mechanics:
  •   <rt.heal>Radiant Runes</> are your Builder/Spender resource
      •   Max 6 Radiant Runes can be held at a time.
      •   Runes are built using certain abilities, such as <rt.Bold>Dawnflare</>.
      •   Radiant Runes are spent to cast powerful spells, such as <rt.Bold>Rune of Renewal</> or <rt.Bold>Luminous Barrier</>.
      •   Many spells that use Radiant Runes can also generate more.

  •   <rt.heal>Direct Healing</> is integral to Vigour’s playstyle
      •   Reactively, Vigour relies on direct healing spells, such as <rt.Bold>Heal</> and <rt.Bold>Circle of Light</> to mend allies.
      •   Proactively, Vigour can use <rt.Bold>Luminous Barrier</> to absorb incoming damage, or use <rt.Bold>Rune of Renewal</> to increase the effectiveness of other healing abilities.

  •   <rt.heal>Spirit Ability - Avatar of Light</>
      •   Vigour instantly heals all of his allies and enters an <rt.Bold>Enlightened state</> for a short duration.
      •   While Enlightened;
           •    The mana cost of <rt.Bold>Radiant Blast, Heal, and Circle of Light</> are halved.
           •    <rt.Bold>Radiant Blast</> and <rt.Bold>Circle of Light</> have no Cooldown.
           •    <rt.Bold>Heal</> is instant cast.
      •   Vigour also gains 30% haste for 20 seconds.

<rt.heal>Vigour Tips:</>
  •   Repeatedly cast <rt.Bold>Dawnflare</> on enemies to generate the Radiant Runes you’ll need to support allies.
  •   Use Radiant Rune Spenders before you generate more than you can use.
  •   Radiant Rune Spenders are best used in certain situations
      •   <rt.Bold>Luminous Barrier</> is useful to prevent an ally from taking damage.
      •   <rt.Bold>Rune of Renewal</> is good at amplifying healing when an ally is taking a lot of damage.
      •   <rt.Bold>Soulbrand</> deals damage over time. It also returns its cost over its duration if the target survives long enough.
      •   <rt.Bold>Dawnbreaker Orb</> is incredibly powerful when you hit multiple enemies and allies with it.
  •   Encourage your allies to stay nearby to maximize the value of <rt.Bold>Radiant Blast</> and <rt.Bold>Circle of Light</>.
  •   Be careful which direction you are facing when you cast <rt.Bold>Radiant Blast</> or <rt.Bold>Dawnbreaker Orb</>.
      •   Be sure to hit your allies and enemies in combat.
      •   Avoid hitting enemies outside of combat that you could accidentally draw into the fight!

<rt.meikoability2>Swing Timer</>
Your swing timer is displayed as a bar to the right of your hero. When you see the red area light up on the swing timer it is time to queue your <rt.absorb>Heavy Strike</> and wait for it to finish.

<rt.meikoability2>Queueing Heavy Strike</>
<rt.absorb>Heavy Strike's</> queue is displayed as a golden border around the ability icon on your action bar. The queue is canceled when you use any other ability, so make sure the last button you press before the swing timer reaches the end of the red area is Heavy Strike.
